President Cyril Ramaphosa will on Wednesday morning give the opening address at the 10th Brics Summit in Sandton, where more than 1 000 delegates, including heads of state and business people, will converge Minister of Trade and Industry Rob Davies and Chairperson of the BRICS Business Council Iqbal Surve will be in attendance. The meeting follows the successful hosting of the sixth annual Brics Council Meeting in Durban and will take place on the sidelines of the Brics Business Forum. READ MORE: SA grants Brics diplomats and business travellers 10-year port of entry visas The two events are part of the 10th Brics Summit, which is hosted by South Africa under the theme ‘’Brics in Africa: Collaboration for Inclusive Growth and Shared Prosperity in the Fourth Industrial Revolution.’’ – African News Agency